race.description: Cecil Taylor Memorial Country Boosted Mdn Plate
race.comment: BIRDY GIRL (3) finished in the minor money at five of her six starts and won't find an easier contest to shed her Maiden status. Launched late from back in the field when third over 1250m at Kempsey. No excuses today. MESS AROUND (11) three-year-old filly by Outreach from Suggest on debut for the Owen stable. Shown ability in the two trials and capable of taking this out. DANDEELION WISHES (6) gripped on late at the big odds when a sound second over 1005m at Taree. Deep into the prep and stays in the contest. BIG STEPPA (2) failed to fire in two career starts and resumes with leading apprentice booked. Didn't do much in the two trials and place claims look best.
